featured_reviews.review_translated_text: It is said that if those attending the court of Hazrat go to pay their obeisance at the saint's tomb, their wish is soon fulfilled. Elders believe that the pilgrimage of the pilgrims who come for the Urs of Hazrat Qutub-e-Alam is also accepted by having darshan of Saint Baba Haridas. Although people come to Hazrat's shrine throughout the year, but on the occasion of Urs, the crowd of pilgrims from states like Haryana, Punjab, Himachal Pradesh, Uttarakhand and Rajasthan increases. On the occasion of Urs, the shrines of Hazrat Qutub-e-Alam, Hazrat Sheikh Sadiq, Hazrat Dawood and Mamu Maula Baksh located here are illuminated. The procession taken out on this occasion is an important part of Jubba Sharif Urs.
